name: soybean meal and crude oil production | soybean oil, crude | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/8945/documentation

This dataset represents the production of 1000 kg crude soybean oil and its respective output of soybean meal. The multioutput-process 'soybeans, in oil mill' delivers the co-products 'crude soybean oil, at oil mill' and 'soybean meal, at oil mill'.;[This dataset is meant to replace the following datasets:; - soybean meal and crude oil production, US, 1998 - 2006 (3b0e1b4c-5379-43cf-af77-1b878cc5e0b9)]

From arrival of the soybeans to the mill through crushing and processing to crude, degummed soybean oil and soybean meal.

The system boundary is at the mill.
category: C:Manufacturing/10:Manufacture of food products/104:Manufacture of vegetable and animal oils and fats/1040:Manufacture of vegetable and animal oils and fats

processDocumentation.timeDescription: Data for 2007: current technology for soybean crushing and processing.
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data collected from 50 of the 60 soybean processing plants in North America that National Oilseed Processors Association represents.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Typical North American oil mill designed for soybean oil solvent extraction (incl. pre-cracking of soybeans, dehulling, oil extraction, meal processing and degumming),
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Primary data - from 50 North American soybean processing plants collected for a year's period.

exchanges.description: Produced during crushing and processing.  Coproduct of soy meal at the mill.
